Serves- 4

Ingredients:
  2 tbsp olive oil
  1 large onion (or leek), chopped
  1 carrot, peeled & chopped
  2 celery sticks, chopped
  ¼ tsp ground cinnamon
  ¼ tsp ground cloves
  500g beetroot, wrapped in foil & roasted whole until tender, the peeled & roughly chopped
  400g fresh/tinned chopped tomatoes
  800ml vegetable stock
  sea salt
  ground black pepper

Heat oil in a large saucepan.
Add the onion, carrot and celery and fry on a low heat for 8 mins, stirring occasionally,to soften without browning.
Add the garlic and fry for 2 mins.
Add cinnamon, cloves, beetroot, tomatoes and stock.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 10-15 mins.
Blend until very smooth.
Put the soup back in the pan.
Reheat gently to serve, season to taste.
